<Options>

<!-- =====================================================================================================================
 The Profiles page does not appear in any menus.  They are only linked to.	

 When the Index page is disabled, the menu home icon will link to your server's root domain, i.e. http://domain.com.  
 Enable to create a table of contents page linked to the home icon.  If you do disable it, you may want to copy 
 your names.html file to index.html so that there is a default page to load.

 The Kinships page does not appear in any menus.  They are only linked to from the Kinship Lines on Profile pages.	
	
 When the Names page is enabled, it creates a master index of all surnames, and individual index with complete names 
 for each letter of the alphabet.
	
 When the Sources page is enabled, it creates a master index of all sources, and individual source profile pages.
 
 When the Articles page is enabled, it creates a master index of all articles, and individual article profile pages.
 Articles are created when using the special _TITL tag in NOTE records (see User Guide) 	
 
 When the Locations page is enabled, it creates a master index of all locations, and individual location profile pages.
 
 When the Map page is enabled, it creates a Population Distribution Heatmap including the location of all events found 
 in your Timeline.
 
 When the Census page is enabled, it creates a master index of all Census Table Reports, and individual Census Table 
 Report pages.  See <Centar> below.

 When the Descendants page is enabled, it creates a master index of all Descendant Lists, and individual Descendant 
 List pages.  See <DList> below.

 When the Generations page is enabled, it creates a master index of all Generation Lists, and individual Generation 
 List pages.  See <GList> below.

 When the Timelines page is enabled, it creates a master index of all timeline eras, and individual timeline era 
 pages including all events found in your GEDCOM file.

 When the Military page is enabled, it creates a master index of all military eras, and individual military era 
 pages including all military events found in your GEDCOM file.
 
 When the Immigrants page is enabled, it creates an Immigrants reports including all immigration events.  See the
 User Guide to see how to get Ship's names added to the report.

 When the Nobility page is enabled, it creates an Nobility Titles reports including all and sort by nobility titles.
 
 When the Photos page is enabled, it creates a Photos page including all multimedia logical records found in your 
 GEDCOM file.  See the User Guide to see how to use this.
 
 When the Bonkers page is enabled, it creates an Data consistency report including all impossible and improbable 
 claims found in your GEDCOM file.
 
 When the Statistics page is enabled, it creates an Statistics report including the most popular given and surnames 
 found in your GEDCOM file along with average ages of first marriage by gender as well as the average years per 
 generation, the average lifespans by gender per century, total record types found, the distribution of claim types,
 and statistics one how many of these are documented.

 When the Updates page is enabled, it creates an Update report including recently modified logical records.  Some 
 applications do not modify the CHANge fields, so not updates ever appear.  In that case you might as well disable
 the page.
 
 Pages 
	Pages wrapper
 P.name
	Page row
 Menu
	the menu display text
 Title
	the tooltip and index display text
 File
	the file name prefix to be used.  as long as you do not change these, or your logical record ids, your page names 
	should remain the same from build to build.
 Enable (default: false)
	indicate if the page should be built and included in the menu 
	
===================================================================================================================== -->
